    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-04-13T16:02:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-04-13T16:02:00-05:00" n="190"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d190">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">330.13/4–1354: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">United States Mission at the United Nations</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d190fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_BECHHOEFERBG1"
                            >Bechhoefer</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-04-13T16:02:00-05:00"
                            >April 13, 1954—4:02 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>483. Verbatim text. Limited distribution. Following is portion of Telegram 4523
                    of April 13 from London, dealing with discussions between Secretary and
                        <persName corresp="#p_EDENSA1">Eden</persName> on UN Disarmament Commission:
                        <pb facs="0571" n="1385" xml:id="pg_1385"/>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“UN Disarmament Commission. <persName corresp="#p_EDENSA1"
                                >Eden</persName> raised possibility of Disarmament Commission
                            meeting in London about May 7. <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> regards
                            this as cold war exercise designed to put Soviets on spot and believes
                            USSR vulnerable since they have always insisted that any sanctions be
                            subject to veto in <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>. <persName
                                corresp="#p_EDENSA1">Eden</persName> thought it important to have
                            disarmament discussions on comprehensive plan in London so that it would
                            not get intermingled with debates in <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>
                            on Arab-Israel and other matters. I told <persName corresp="#p_EDENSA1"
                                >Eden</persName> that if it would help <gloss target="#t_UK1"
                                >UK</gloss> to have discussions in London I would go along. I also
                            told him that I thought Disarmament Commission talks should be separate
                            from discussions on President’s December 8 proposal re atomic energy
                            which was a different aspect of atomic problem and should be carried on
                            through diplomatic channels, at least for coming period. <persName
                                corresp="#p_EDENSA1">Eden</persName> agreed. Re report that
                            suggestion might be made for Disarmament Commission to meet in Paris
                            rather than London, <persName corresp="#p_EDENSA1">Eden</persName> and I
                            both agreed that meeting in Paris would be most unwise. <persName
                                corresp="#p_EDENSA1">Eden</persName> commented that meeting in
                            London would get <persName corresp="#p_MOCHJ1">Jules Moch</persName> out
                            of Paris which would be helpful for <gloss target="#t_EDC1"
                            >EDC</gloss>”.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SMITHGWB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
